You current expression is getting the position of all `tr` elements (because the ancestor axis applies to only `table` element).

If you want the position of the parent `tr`, it might be easiest to simply set a variable holding the position prior to the `xsl:for-each` like so:

    &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;tr&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;pos&quot; select=&quot;position()&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;xsl:for-each select=&quot;.&quot;&gt;
            &lt;tps:context id=&quot;{$pos}&quot; type=&quot;{translate(td[2],&#39; &#39;,&#39;&#39;)}&quot;&gt;
                &lt;tps:image&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;&#39;../../../Images/Wind_1.eps&#39;&quot;/&gt;
                &lt;/tps:image&gt;
            &lt;/tps:context&gt;
        &lt;/xsl:for-each&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:template&gt;

This does assume you are wither striping out whitespace with `xsl:strip-space`, or doing an `&lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;tr /&gt;&quot;`, to avoid including whitespace nodes in the count. If you don&#39;t strip out whitespace, and do `&lt;xsl:apply-templates /&gt;` when positioned on the parent `table` element, then the whitespace text nodes between the `tr` elements will be selected, and this affects the result of the `position()` function.

Alternatively, change the variable to this:

    &lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;pos&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:number /&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:variable&gt;

Having said that, I am not sure of the need for `xsl:for-each select&quot;.&quot;`. You could just do this (again with the assumption whitespace has been stripped out).

    &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;tr&quot;&gt;
        &lt;tps:context id=&quot;{position()}&quot; type=&quot;{translate(td[2],&#39; &#39;,&#39;&#39;)}&quot;&gt;
            &lt;tps:image&gt;
                &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;&#39;../../../Images/Wind_1.eps&#39;&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/tps:image&gt;
        &lt;/tps:context&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:template&gt;

See this in action at http://xsltfiddle.liberty-development.net/bFWR5DX (Note the use of `xsl:strip-space` in the XSLT).

Or, if you are not stripping out whitespace, do this

    &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;tr&quot;&gt;
      &lt;xsl:variable name=&quot;pos&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:number /&gt;
      &lt;/xsl:variable&gt;
      &lt;tps:context id=&quot;{$pos}&quot; type=&quot;{translate(td[2],&#39; &#39;,&#39;&#39;)}&quot;&gt;
        &lt;tps:image&gt;
          &lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;&#39;../../../Images/Wind_1.eps&#39;&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/tps:image&gt;
      &lt;/tps:context&gt;
